<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I moved from using vanilla <code>ansi-term</code> to using <code>multi-term</code>.</p> <p>One very nice feature about <code>ansi-term</code> was how I could press <code>C-c C-j</code> to change from <code>term-char-mode</code> to <code>term-line-mode</code> and then press <code>C-c C-k</code> again to come back to <code>term-char-mode</code>.</p> <p>After installing the <code>C-c C-j</code> command does not work anymore when I am in <code>term-char-mode</code>. I have to run <code>M-x term-line-mode RET</code> now to change to <code>term-line-mode</code>.</p> <p>How can I get back the <code>C-c C-j</code> behavior to change from <code>term-char-mode</code> to <code>term-line-mode</code>?</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/sparklingsphere"> /u/sparklingsphere </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/wj5i0e/how_to_use_cc_cj_to_switch_to_termlinemode_while/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/wj5i0e/how_to_use_cc_cj_to_switch_to_termlinemode_while/">[comments]</a></span>